description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education: Simulation Centre Specialist Lead&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barts Health Simulation team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based at Newham Simulation Centre&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 8a&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WTE - 37.5 Hours . Mon- Friday &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of Barts Health NHS Trust, Newham is one of 5 hospitals which make up the Trust. Barts Health can boast some of the most innovative approaches to Medical Education in the U.K. Following considerable investment in facilities and equipment the Trust has access to extensive and high quality training equipment, and experienced faculty to deliver this education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Simulation and Essential Clinical Skills service forms part of the Education Academy within Barts Health. It is responsible for providing facilities and educational opportunities for both undergraduate and post graduate trainees across Barts Health. The successful candidate will lead a team that includes clinical skills tutors, and Education Academy Fellows who deliver the education and training at that site around simulation based training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking to recruit to the position of Simulation Centre Lead post who will have the skills to lead at this site for simulation and essential clinical skills. The post holder will be involved in the wider remit of team training and debriefing in the clinical areas in response to both planned insitu education and real life clinical incidents. The post holder will work as part of the wider simulation team based across all 4 simulation centres and work alongside .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of this role the post holder will be required to design, develop, deliver &amp; evaluate Clinical Education Programmes which encompass essential clinical skills, high fidelity simulation, haptic skills training, human factors, communications skills &amp; patient safety training. They will support the trusts long term strategy to embed a culture of Patient Safety &amp; Human factors awareness through all educational programmes and be able to promote &amp; support an active and responsive approach to training &amp; development across the Trust through clinical, human factors &amp; communication skills, &amp; simulation based learning initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be based in the Simulation Centre at Newham University Hospital, however they will be expected to work across the 3 Trust sites as necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WHAT WE’RE LOOKING FOR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A registered nurse/midwife&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Someone with a degree and working towards/ completed master’s programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in teaching / simulation based training and Human Factors teaching.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage their own workload / services and manage a large team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and social skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aptitude for learning and best practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work both within a team and independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WHAT WE CAN OFFER&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive orientation and development programme which will include opportunity to shadow work across all Simulation centres&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Time to ‘grow’ into the post&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education and learning opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Part of an effective and friendly team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;INTERESTED?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rachel Gill, Associate Director for Simulation and Essential Clinical Skills at Rachel.gill9@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
